summary: Emma will be home soon and she will let Will know.

dialogue.speaker: Will
dialogue.text: Will: hey babe, what do you want for dinner tonight?

dialogue.speaker: Emma
dialogue.text: Emma:  gah, don't even worry about it tonight

dialogue.speaker: Will
dialogue.text: Will: what do you mean? everything ok?

dialogue.speaker: Emma
dialogue.text: Emma: not really, but it's ok, don't worry about cooking though, I'm not hungry

dialogue.speaker: Will
dialogue.text: Will: Well what time will you be home?

dialogue.speaker: Emma
dialogue.text: Emma: soon, hopefully

dialogue.speaker: Will
dialogue.text: Will: you sure? Maybe you want me to pick you up?

dialogue.speaker: Will
dialogue.text: Will: Alright, love you.

dialogue.text: Emma: love you too.

summary: Jane is in Warsaw. Ollie and Jane has a party. Jane lost her calendar. They will get a lunch this week on Friday. Ollie accidentally called Jane and talked about whisky. Jane cancels lunch. They'll meet for a tea at 6 pm.

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: Hi , are you in Warsaw

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: yes, just back! Btw are you free for diner the 19th?

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: nope!

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: and the  18th?

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: nope, we have this party and you must be there, remember?

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: oh right! i lost my calendar..  thanks for reminding me

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: we have lunch this week?

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: with pleasure!

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: friday?

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: ok

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: what do you mean " we don't have any more whisky!" lol..

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: what!!!

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: you just call me and the all thing i heard was that sentence about whisky... what's wrong with you?

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: oh oh... very strange! i have to be carefull may be there is some spy in my mobile! lol

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: dont' worry, we'll check on friday.

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: don't forget to bring some sun with you

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: I can't wait to be in Morocco..

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: enjoy and see you friday

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: sorry Ollie, i'm very busy, i won't have time for lunch  tomorrow, but may be at 6pm after my courses?this trip to Morocco was so nice, but time consuming!

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: ok for tea!

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: I'm on my way..

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: tea is ready, did you bring the pastries?

dialogue.speaker: Jane
dialogue.text: Jane: I already ate them all... see you in a minute

dialogue.speaker: Ollie
dialogue.text: Ollie: ok

summary: Hilary has the keys to the apartment. Benjamin wants to get them and go take a nap. Hilary is having lunch with some French people at La Cantina. Hilary is meeting them at the entrance to the conference hall at 2 pm. Benjamin and Elliot might join them. They're meeting for the drinks in the evening.

dialogue.speaker: Benjamin
dialogue.text: Benjamin: Hey guys, what are we doing with the keys today?

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: I've got them. Whoever wants them can meet me at lunchtime or after

dialogue.speaker: Elliot
dialogue.text: Elliot: I'm ok. We're meeting for the drinks in the evening anyway and I guess we'll be going back to the apartment together?

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: Yeah, I guess so

dialogue.speaker: Daniel
dialogue.text: Daniel: I'm with Hilary atm and won't let go of her for the rest of the day, so any option you guys choose is good for me

dialogue.speaker: Benjamin
dialogue.text: Benjamin: Hmm I might actually pass by at lunchtime, take the keys and go take a nap. I'm sooo tired after yesterday

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: Sounds good. We'll be having lunch with some French people (the ones who work on the history of food in colonial Mexico - I already see you yawning your head off)

dialogue.speaker: Benjamin
dialogue.text: Benjamin: YAAAAWN 🙊 Where and where are you meeting?

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: So I'm meeting them at the entrance to the conference hall at 2 pm and then we'll head to this place called La Cantina. Italian cuisine, which is quite funny, but that's what they've chosen

dialogue.speaker: Benjamin
dialogue.text: Benjamin: Interesting 😱 To be honest, Hilary, I almost feel like changing my mind. Wanting to take this nap might end up costing me to dear

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: Oh come on 😂

dialogue.speaker: Benjamin
dialogue.text: Benjamin: All these terrible obstacles on mu way to bed might just prove to much to take

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: We'll try to avoid talking about their subject of research. Oh wait, no, I'm actually meeting them because I wanted to chat about their research lol

dialogue.speaker: Elliot
dialogue.text: Elliot: 🙉

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: Do join us, we're going to have fun. And then you'll take the keys and take this most deserved of naps

dialogue.speaker: Elliot
dialogue.text: Elliot: Sounds like a plan 😂

dialogue.speaker: Hilary
dialogue.text: Hilary: 😎

dialogue.speaker: Elliot
dialogue.text: Elliot: See you at 2 then xx

summary: Payton provides Max with websites selling clothes. Payton likes browsing and trying on the clothes but not necessarily buying them. Payton usually buys clothes and books as he loves reading.

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Know any good sites to buy clothes from?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Sure :) <file_other> <file_other> <file_other> <file_other> <file_other> <file_other> <file_other>

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: That's a lot of them!

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Yeah, but they have different things so I usually buy things from 2 or 3 of them.

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: I'll check them out. Thanks.

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: No problem :)

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: How about u?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: What about me?

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Do u like shopping?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Yes and no.

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: How come?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: I like browsing, trying on, looking in the mirror and seeing how I look, but not always buying.

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Y not?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Isn't it obvious? ;)

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Sry ;)

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: If I bought everything I liked, I'd have nothing left to live on ;)

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Same here, but probably different category ;)

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Lol

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: So what do u usually buy?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Well, I have 2 things I must struggle to resist!

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Which are?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Clothes, ofc ;)

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Right. And the second one?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Books. I absolutely love reading!

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Gr8! What books do u read?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Everything I can get my hands on :)

dialogue.speaker: Max
dialogue.text: Max: Srsly?

dialogue.speaker: Payton
dialogue.text: Payton: Yup :)

summary: Rita and Tina are bored at work and have still 4 hours left.

dialogue.speaker: Rita
dialogue.text: Rita: I'm so bloody tired. Falling asleep at work. :-(

dialogue.speaker: Tina
dialogue.text: Tina: I know what you mean.

dialogue.speaker: Tina
dialogue.text: Tina: I keep on nodding off at my keyboard hoping that the boss doesn't notice..

dialogue.speaker: Rita
dialogue.text: Rita: The time just keeps on dragging on and on and on....

dialogue.speaker: Rita
dialogue.text: Rita: I keep on looking at the clock and there's still 4 hours of this drudgery to go.

dialogue.speaker: Tina
dialogue.text: Tina: Times like these I really hate my work.

dialogue.speaker: Rita
dialogue.text: Rita: I'm really not cut out for this level of boredom.

dialogue.speaker: Tina
dialogue.text: Tina: Neither am I.

summary: Beatrice wants to buy Leo a scarf, but he doesn't like scarves. She cares about his health and will buy him a scarf no matter his opinion.

dialogue.speaker: Beatrice
dialogue.text: Beatrice: I am in town, shopping. They have nice scarfs in the shop next to the church. Do you want one?

dialogue.speaker: Leo
dialogue.text: Leo: No, thanks

dialogue.speaker: Beatrice
dialogue.text: Beatrice: But you don't have a scarf.

dialogue.speaker: Leo
dialogue.text: Leo: Because I don't need it.

dialogue.speaker: Beatrice
dialogue.text: Beatrice: Last winter you had a cold all the time. A scarf could help.

dialogue.speaker: Leo
dialogue.text: Leo: I don't like them.

dialogue.speaker: Beatrice
dialogue.text: Beatrice: Actually, I don't care. You will get a scarf.

dialogue.speaker: Leo
dialogue.text: Leo: How understanding of you!

dialogue.speaker: Beatrice
dialogue.text: Beatrice: You were complaining the whole winter that you're going to die. I've had enough.

dialogue.speaker: Leo
dialogue.text: Leo: Eh.
